===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=psc|日|c1=s|t1=sun; day|之|c2=p|t2=to go}} — the passing of time.

In ancient scripts, it had the form {{zh-l|*旹}}. The phonetic component later changed to {{och-l|*寺}}.

===Etymology===
; "time", "duration"
: From {{och-l|之|to go; to proceed}} + endopassive voicing + endoactive tone B (OC *''-ʔ'' > expected MC {{zh-l|*上聲}}), literally “that which is proceeding” ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). The glottal stop was however lost, probably due to confusion with the pronoun sense.
; "this"
: An [[unemphatic]] form of {{och-l|是|this}} ({{zh-ref|Pulleybank, 1995}}). Cognate with {{och-l|之|this; ''third-person pronoun''}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

